summary:
Working towards strengthening health systems around the world. A history of working around different areas of the health care systems and a wide range of travels have led me to find a nexus the two. I'm passionate about working with health care systems around the world to build on their capacities through interventions that are locally informed and address system dynamics. I am actively searching for a new role that will help me to grow further in this field. 

I've recently graduated from the Master of Health Economics, Policy and Law graduate from the Erasmus University Rotterdam, and have been working with a Dutch global development agency to better understand how their performance based financing program is contributing to the realization of the WHO health system building blocks. Hands on research experience in Ethiopia and Indonesia have provided me with a broader understanding of different health contexts and allowed me to build on a range of skills in challenging environments. 

In my personal time, I love sport, the arts and the outdoors. I am an avid cyclist, backcountry skier, surfer, climber, and played on the varsity water polo team during my bachelor degree. I enjoy the arts, and have experimented with different mediums such as oil, acrylic and water colour painting, as well as multi-media design. I love art history and am a keen reader. Lastly, I have developed a strong connection with the outdoors through my parents and further enhanced through my sporting interests.
